Remediation: The return value of a message call is not checked.

Avoid strict equality checks for the Ether balance in a contract. Contracts can behave erroneously when they strictly assume a specific Ether balance. It is always possible to forcibly send ether to a contract (without triggering its fallback function), using selfdestruct, or by mining to the account. In the worst case scenario this could lead to DOS conditions that might render the contract unusa-ble. refer to https://swcregistry.io/docs/SWC-132/#lockdropsol
